[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] is one in which every two vertices on opposite sides of the partition of vertices are adjacent.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] A completion of a given graph is a supergraph that has some desired property.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] is a supergraph that is a chordal graph.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] is a proper coloring in which each pairs of colors is used for the endpoints of at least one edge.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Every coloring with a minimum number of colors is complete, but there may exist complete colorings with larger numbers of colors.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] A complete invariant of a graph is a synonym for a canonical form, an invariant that has different values for non-isomorphic graphs.
