[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] Information associated with a vertex or edge of a graph.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A labeled graph is a graph whose vertices or edges have labels.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] may be used to specify which objects of a graph have labels.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] refers to several different problems of assigning labels to graphs subject to certain constraints.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] , in which the labels are interpreted as colors.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] , the vertices of a graph are said to be labeled if they are all distinguishable from each other.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] For instance, this can be made to be true by fixing a one-to-one correspondence between the vertices and the integers from 1 to the order of the graph.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] When vertices are labeled, graphs that are isomorphic to each other (but with different vertex orderings) are counted as separate objects.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] In contrast, when the vertices are unlabeled, graphs that are isomorphic to each other are not counted separately.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A leaf edge or pendant edge is the edge connecting a leaf vertex to its single neighbour.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] of a tree is a graph whose vertices are the leaves of the tree and whose edges connect leaves whose distance in the tree is at most a given threshold.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] In an unweighted graph, the length of a cycle, path, or walk is the number of edges it uses.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] In a weighted graph, it may instead be the sum of the weights of the edges that it uses.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A node's level in a rooted tree is the number of nodes in the path from the root to the node.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] For instance, the root has level 1 and any one of its adjacent nodes has level 2.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A set of all node having the same level or depth.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a computer representation of graphs for use in graph algorithms.
