[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A regular tournament is a tournament where in-degree equals out-degree for all vertices.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a form of logic in which variables may represent vertices, edges, sets of vertices, and (sometimes) sets of edges.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] This logic includes predicates for testing whether a vertex and edge are incident, as well as whether a vertex or edge belongs to a set.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] To be distinguished from first order logic, in which variables can only represent vertices.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a graph without loops and without multiple adjacencies.
