[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A simple edge is an edge that is not part of a multiple adjacency.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] In many cases, graphs are assumed to be simple unless specified otherwise.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A simple path or a simple cycle is a path or cycle that has no repeated vertices and consequently no repeated edges.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A sink, in a directed graph, is a vertex with no outgoing edges (out-degree equals 0).
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a graph in which most nodes are not neighbors of one another, but most nodes can be reached from every other node by a small number of hops or steps.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a simple, connected, bridgeless cubic graph with chromatic index equal to 4.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A source, in a directed graph, is a vertex with no incoming edges (in-degree equals 0).
