[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] has the Eulerian spanning subgraphs as its elements.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A spanner is a (usually sparse) graph whose shortest path distances approximate those in a dense graph or other metric space.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] , spanning trees of a graph whose distances approximate the graph distances, and graph spanners, sparse subgraphs of a dense graph whose distances approximate the original graph's distances.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A greedy spanner is a graph spanner constructed by a greedy algorithm, generally one that considers all edges from shortest to longest and keeps the ones that are needed to preserve the distance approximation.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A subgraph is spanning when it includes all of the vertices of the given graph.
