[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] of a graph is a minimal graph having the same transitive closure; directed acyclic graphs have a unique transitive reduction.
[src:floyd-warshall-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] of a given directed graph is a graph on the same vertices, with each edge reversed in direction.
